{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":816,"text":"We all go to doctors."},{"time":4944,"text":"And we do so with trust and blind faith"},{"time":9306,"text":"that the test they are ordering\nand the medications they're prescribing"},{"time":13188,"text":"are based upon evidence --"},{"time":16387,"text":"evidence that's designed to help us."},{"time":20338,"text":"However, the reality is that that hasn't\nalways been the case for everyone."},{"time":27086,"text":"What if I told you"},{"time":28405,"text":"that the medical science discovered\nover the past century"},{"time":32375,"text":"has been based on only\nhalf the population?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36066,"text":"I'm an emergency medicine doctor."},{"time":38749,"text":"I was trained to be prepared\nin a medical emergency."},{"time":42940,"text":"It's about saving lives. How cool is that?"},{"time":48492,"text":"OK, there's a lot of runny noses\nand stubbed toes,"},{"time":51676,"text":"but no matter who walks\nthrough the door to the ER,"},{"time":55365,"text":"we order the same tests,"},{"time":57841,"text":"we prescribe the same medication,"},{"time":59999,"text":"without ever thinking about the sex\nor gender of our patients."},{"time":65370,"text":"Why would we?"},{"time":67053,"text":"We were never taught that there were\nany differences between men and women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70818,"text":"A recent Government Accountability study\nrevealed that 80 percent of the drugs"},{"time":75401,"text":"withdrawn from the market"},{"time":77576,"text":"are due to side effects on women."},{"time":81080,"text":"So let's think about that for a minute."},{"time":83415,"text":"Why are we discovering\nside effects on women"},{"time":87313,"text":"only after a drug has been\nreleased to the market?"},{"time":91496,"text":"Do you know that it takes years\nfor a drug to go from an idea"},{"time":97180,"text":"to being tested on cells in a laboratory,"},{"time":100361,"text":"to animal studies,"},{"time":102353,"text":"to then clinical trials on humans,"},{"time":104504,"text":"finally to go through\na regulatory approval process,"},{"time":108399,"text":"to be available for your doctor\nto prescribe to you?"},{"time":114170,"text":"Not to mention the millions and billions\nof dollars of funding"},{"time":117564,"text":"it takes to go through that process."},{"time":121597,"text":"So why are we discovering\nunacceptable side effects"},{"time":124573,"text":"on half the population\nafter that has gone through?"},{"time":131163,"text":"What's happening?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":132777,"text":"Well, it turns out that those cells\nused in that laboratory,"},{"time":136905,"text":"they're male cells,"},{"time":138859,"text":"and the animals used\nin the animal studies were male animals,"},{"time":142285,"text":"and the clinical trials have been\nperformed almost exclusively on men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149176,"text":"How is it that the male model became\nour framework for medical research?"},{"time":154554,"text":"Let's look at an example that has been\npopularized in the media,"},{"time":158649,"text":"and it has to do\nwith the sleep aid Ambien."},{"time":161879,"text":"Ambien was released on the market\nover 20 years ago,"},{"time":166667,"text":"and since then, hundreds of millions\nof prescriptions have been written,"},{"time":171504,"text":"primarily to women, because women\nsuffer more sleep disorders than men."},{"time":177047,"text":"But just this past year,"},{"time":179247,"text":"the Food and Drug Administration\nrecommended cutting the dose in half"},{"time":182695,"text":"for women only,"},{"time":185606,"text":"because they just realized\nthat women metabolize the drug"},{"time":188467,"text":"at a slower rate than men,"},{"time":191404,"text":"causing them to wake up in the morning"},{"time":193467,"text":"with more of the active drug\nin their system."},{"time":196685,"text":"And then they're drowsy and they're\ngetting behind the wheel of the car,"},{"time":200639,"text":"and they're at risk\nfor motor vehicle accidents."},{"time":204955,"text":"And I can't help but think,\nas an emergency physician,"},{"time":208923,"text":"how many of my patients\nthat I've cared for over the years"},{"time":213740,"text":"were involved in a motor vehicle accident"},{"time":216570,"text":"that possibly could have been prevented"},{"time":220046,"text":"if this type of analysis was performed\nand acted upon 20 years ago"},{"time":225185,"text":"when this drug was first released."},{"time":229089,"text":"How many other things need\nto be analyzed by gender?"},{"time":233197,"text":"What else are we missing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237555,"text":"World War II changed a lot of things,"},{"time":241255,"text":"and one of them was this need\nto protect people"},{"time":244160,"text":"from becoming victims of medical research\nwithout informed consent."},{"time":249467,"text":"So some much-needed guidelines\nor rules were set into place,"},{"time":253167,"text":"and part of that was this desire\nto protect women of childbearing age"},{"time":258213,"text":"from entering into any\nmedical research studies."},{"time":262016,"text":"There was fear: what if something\nhappened to the fetus during the study?"},{"time":267366,"text":"Who would be responsible?"},{"time":269999,"text":"And so the scientists\nat this time actually thought"},{"time":272512,"text":"this was a blessing in disguise,"},{"time":275152,"text":"because let's face it -- men's bodies\nare pretty homogeneous."},{"time":280867,"text":"They don't have the constantly\nfluctuating levels of hormones"},{"time":284337,"text":"that could disrupt clean data\nthey could get if they had only men."},{"time":289210,"text":"It was easier. It was cheaper."},{"time":293651,"text":"Not to mention, at this time,\nthere was a general assumption"},{"time":296508,"text":"that men and women\nwere alike in every way,"},{"time":300757,"text":"apart from their reproductive organs\nand sex hormones."},{"time":305211,"text":"So it was decided:"},{"time":309117,"text":"medical research was performed on men,"},{"time":312657,"text":"and the results were later\napplied to women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317203,"text":"What did this do to the notion\nof women's health?"},{"time":320768,"text":"Women's health became synonymous\nwith reproduction:"},{"time":325048,"text":"breasts, ovaries, uterus, pregnancy."},{"time":330355,"text":"It's this term we now refer\nto as \"bikini medicine.\""},{"time":334461,"text":"And this stayed this way\nuntil about the 1980s,"},{"time":337129,"text":"when this concept was challenged\nby the medical community"},{"time":340638,"text":"and by the public health policymakers\nwhen they realized that"},{"time":344803,"text":"by excluding women\nfrom all medical research studies"},{"time":349130,"text":"we actually did them a disservice,"},{"time":352643,"text":"in that apart from reproductive issues,"},{"time":354999,"text":"virtually nothing was known\nabout the unique needs"},{"time":357587,"text":"of the female patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360999,"text":"Since that time, an overwhelming amount\nof evidence has come to light"},{"time":366537,"text":"that shows us just how different\nmen and women are in every way."},{"time":377297,"text":"You know, we have this saying in medicine:"},{"time":380074,"text":"children are not just little adults."},{"time":384810,"text":"And we say that to remind ourselves"},{"time":386771,"text":"that children actually have\na different physiology than normal adults."},{"time":392678,"text":"And it's because of this that the medical\nspecialty of pediatrics came to light."},{"time":397659,"text":"And we now conduct research on children\nin order to improve their lives."},{"time":405039,"text":"And I know the same thing\ncan be said about women."},{"time":407960,"text":"Women are not just men\nwith boobs and tubes."},{"time":414561,"text":"But they have their own\nanatomy and physiology"},{"time":418141,"text":"that deserves to be studied\nwith the same intensity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423381,"text":"Let's take the cardiovascular\nsystem, for example."},{"time":426999,"text":"This area in medicine has done the most\nto try to figure out"},{"time":430730,"text":"why it seems men and women have\ncompletely different heart attacks."},{"time":435999,"text":"Heart disease is the number one killer\nfor both men and women,"},{"time":441113,"text":"but more women die within the first year\nof having a heart attack than men."},{"time":447049,"text":"Men will complain\nof crushing chest pain --"},{"time":451087,"text":"an elephant is sitting on their chest."},{"time":454455,"text":"And we call this typical."},{"time":457622,"text":"Women have chest pain, too."},{"time":460736,"text":"But more women than men\nwill complain of \"just not feeling right,\""},{"time":468898,"text":"\"can't seem to get enough air in,\""},{"time":471791,"text":"\"just so tired lately.\""},{"time":475000,"text":"And for some reason we call this atypical,"},{"time":477927,"text":"even though, as I mentioned,\nwomen do make up half the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483537,"text":"And so what is some of the evidence\nto help explain some of these differences?"},{"time":489999,"text":"If we look at the anatomy,"},{"time":492554,"text":"the blood vessels that surround the heart\nare smaller in women compared to men,"},{"time":498593,"text":"and the way that those blood vessels\ndevelop disease is different"},{"time":503097,"text":"in women compared to men."},{"time":505875,"text":"And the test that we use to determine\nif someone is at risk for a heart attack,"},{"time":511051,"text":"well, they were initially designed\nand tested and perfected in men,"},{"time":515647,"text":"and so aren't as good\nat determining that in women."},{"time":520305,"text":"And then if we think\nabout the medications --"},{"time":523266,"text":"common medications\nthat we use, like aspirin."},{"time":527767,"text":"We give aspirin to healthy men to help\nprevent them from having a heart attack,"},{"time":532318,"text":"but do you know that if you\ngive aspirin to a healthy woman,"},{"time":536576,"text":"it's actually harmful?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540376,"text":"What this is doing is merely telling us"},{"time":542782,"text":"that we are scratching the surface."},{"time":547145,"text":"Emergency medicine\nis a fast-paced business."},{"time":551563,"text":"In how many life-saving areas of medicine,"},{"time":554940,"text":"like cancer and stroke,"},{"time":558940,"text":"are there important differences between\nmen and women that we could be utilizing?"},{"time":564252,"text":"Or even, why is it that some people\nget those runny noses"},{"time":569080,"text":"more than others,"},{"time":571289,"text":"or why the pain medication that we give\nto those stubbed toes"},{"time":574640,"text":"work in some and not in others?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581288,"text":"The Institute of Medicine has said\nevery cell has a sex."},{"time":587820,"text":"What does this mean?"},{"time":590532,"text":"Sex is DNA."},{"time":592954,"text":"Gender is how someone\npresents themselves in society."},{"time":597883,"text":"And these two may not always match up,"},{"time":600447,"text":"as we can see with our\ntransgendered population."},{"time":604740,"text":"But it's important to realize\nthat from the moment of conception,"},{"time":609679,"text":"every cell in our bodies --"},{"time":611825,"text":"skin, hair, heart and lungs --"},{"time":615150,"text":"contains our own unique DNA,"},{"time":618461,"text":"and that DNA contains\nthe chromosomes that determine"},{"time":622236,"text":"whether we become\nmale or female, man or woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628400,"text":"It used to be thought"},{"time":630012,"text":"that those sex-determining\nchromosomes pictured here --"},{"time":634364,"text":"XY if you're male, XX if you're female --"},{"time":637761,"text":"merely determined whether you\nwould be born with ovaries or testes,"},{"time":642999,"text":"and it was the sex hormones\nthat those organs produced"},{"time":646764,"text":"that were responsible for the differences\nwe see in the opposite sex."},{"time":652757,"text":"But we now know that\nthat theory was wrong --"},{"time":657615,"text":"or it's at least a little incomplete."},{"time":660084,"text":"And thankfully, scientists like Dr. Page\nfrom the Whitehead Institute,"},{"time":664886,"text":"who works on the Y chromosome,"},{"time":666884,"text":"and Doctor Yang from UCLA,"},{"time":669075,"text":"they have found evidence that tells us\nthat those sex-determining chromosomes"},{"time":674758,"text":"that are in every cell in our bodies"},{"time":677379,"text":"continue to remain active\nfor our entire lives"},{"time":684517,"text":"and could be what's responsible\nfor the differences we see"},{"time":688116,"text":"in the dosing of drugs,"},{"time":690355,"text":"or why there are differences\nbetween men and women"},{"time":693345,"text":"in the susceptibility\nand severity of diseases."},{"time":699032,"text":"This new knowledge is the game-changer,"},{"time":705425,"text":"and it's up to those scientists\nthat continue to find that evidence,"},{"time":708823,"text":"but it's up to the clinicians\nto start translating this data"},{"time":713000,"text":"at the bedside, today."},{"time":717168,"text":"Right now."},{"time":721450,"text":"And to help do this, I'm a co-founder\nof a national organization"},{"time":724498,"text":"called Sex and Gender\nWomen's Health Collaborative,"},{"time":727505,"text":"and we collect all of this data\nso that it's available for teaching"},{"time":732149,"text":"and for patient care."},{"time":734380,"text":"And we're working to bring together\nthe medical educators to the table."},{"time":739756,"text":"That's a big job."},{"time":742162,"text":"It's changing the way medical training\nhas been done since its inception."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749039,"text":"But I believe in them."},{"time":751882,"text":"I know they're going to see the value\nof incorporating the gender lens"},{"time":757503,"text":"into the current curriculum."},{"time":760598,"text":"It's about training the future\nhealth care providers correctly."},{"time":768437,"text":"And regionally,"},{"time":769612,"text":"I'm a co-creator of a division within\nthe Department of Emergency Medicine"},{"time":773497,"text":"here at Brown University,"},{"time":775241,"text":"called Sex and Gender\nin Emergency Medicine,"},{"time":777875,"text":"and we conduct the research to determine\nthe differences between men and women"},{"time":782525,"text":"in emergent conditions,"},{"time":784707,"text":"like heart disease and stroke\nand sepsis and substance abuse,"},{"time":789999,"text":"but we also believe\nthat education is paramount."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795304,"text":"We've created a 360-degree\nmodel of education."},{"time":799329,"text":"We have programs for the doctors,\nfor the nurses, for the students"},{"time":805311,"text":"and for the patients."},{"time":807511,"text":"Because this cannot just be left up\nto the health care leaders."},{"time":812315,"text":"We all have a role in making a difference."},{"time":816650,"text":"But I must warn you: this is not easy."},{"time":821840,"text":"In fact, it's hard."},{"time":825146,"text":"It's essentially changing the way\nwe think about medicine"},{"time":829562,"text":"and health and research."},{"time":833711,"text":"It's changing our relationship\nto the health care system."},{"time":837760,"text":"But there's no going back."},{"time":841339,"text":"We now know just enough"},{"time":845062,"text":"to know that we weren't doing it right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849672,"text":"Martin Luther King, Jr. has said,"},{"time":852014,"text":"\"Change does not roll in\non the wheels of inevitability,"},{"time":856687,"text":"but comes through continuous struggle.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":860314,"text":"And the first step\ntowards change is awareness."},{"time":864116,"text":"This is not just about improving\nmedical care for women."},{"time":868702,"text":"This is about personalized,\nindividualized health care for everyone."},{"time":875090,"text":"This awareness has the power to transform\nmedical care for men and women."},{"time":882827,"text":"And from now on, I want you\nto ask your doctors"},{"time":888539,"text":"whether the treatments you are receiving\nare specific to your sex and gender."},{"time":894246,"text":"They may not know the answer --"},{"time":896959,"text":"yet."},{"time":899101,"text":"But the conversation has begun,\nand together we can all learn."},{"time":903797,"text":"Remember, for me\nand my colleagues in this field,"},{"time":908198,"text":"your sex and gender matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911379,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912555,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}